vidence suggests that South African wet blues are smaller and of a somewhat lower quality than those available on the international market.  It is thus highly unlikely that the local OEMs would tolerate a premium on the price of local leather \'96 their MIDP 
incentive may incline them in this direction, but the ability of their parent companies to substitute from suppliers elsewhere in the world will place a strict limit on the premium that they will accept.}
